The folks at Baseball America revealed their top 10 Dodgers prospects heading into the 2017 season on Friday, with first baseman and outfielder Cody Bellinger topping the list.

Bellinger, 21, hit.271/.365/.507 with 26 home runs in 117 games in 2016, all but three games with Double-A Tulsa. He finished up the season with three games with Triple-A Oklahoma City then continued with OKC during the Pacific Coast League
